<%- include('partials/header', { pageTitle, activePage }) %>
<section class="hero-section">
  <div class="container hero-grid">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <h1>Blood Donation Management System</h1>
      <p>
        A compact, responsive web application for donor registration, donor search,
        and admin-side donor management built with HTML, CSS, Vanilla JavaScript,
        Node.js, Express.js, and MySQL.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/register">Register as Donor</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/search">Search Donor</a>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-strip">
        <div>
          <strong>3</strong>
          <span>Core user flows</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>100%</strong>
          <span>Responsive layout</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>1</strong>
          <span>Simple deployment path</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <aside class="hero-panel card-panel">
      <h2>Why this system matters</h2>
      <ul class="check-list">
        <li>It reduces time spent finding matching donors during urgent cases.</li>
        <li>It stores donor information in a structured MySQL database.</li>
        <li>It gives the admin a central dashboard to manage registrations.</li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <span class="eyebrow">Awareness</span>
      <h2>Blood Donation Awareness</h2>
      <p>
        A healthy donation culture depends on awareness, trust, and fast access to donor data.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-grid">
      <article class="info-card">
        <h3>One donation can save lives</h3>
        <p>Regular blood donation helps hospitals maintain a ready supply for emergencies and surgeries.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="info-card">
        <h3>Search by blood group and city</h3>
        <p>Matching donors quickly becomes easier when the database is organised and searchable.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="info-card">
        <h3>Admin control</h3>
        <p>The admin dashboard keeps the records clean by allowing review and deletion of invalid entries.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-block muted-block">
  <div class="container roadmap-grid">
    <div>
      <span class="eyebrow">Project Flow</span>
      <h2>How the application works</h2>
      <ol class="flow-list">
        <li>User opens the home page and reads the awareness section.</li>
        <li>Donor fills the registration form and the data is stored in MySQL.</li>
        <li>Search page helps users locate donors by blood group and city.</li>
        <li>Admin logs in, reviews all donors, and can delete outdated records.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    <div class="mini-card">
      <h3>Quick Navigation</h3>
      <p>Use the menu above to move between registration, search, and admin pages.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions compact-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/register">Get Started</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/admin/login">Admin Login</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<%- include('partials/footer') %>
